The paper discusses wireless transmission using non-contiguous chunks of spectrum, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of Multi-Channel Multi-Radio (MCMR) platforms and Non-Contiguous Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiple Access (NC-OFDMA) technology also suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM) and system engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses cognitive radio networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.CR).
